            title: "Great experience if you plan it correctly",
            rating: 5,
            helpfulVotes: 0,
            text: "Universal Studios Japan is a very fun place but can be a bit hectic as well. If you plan it right you can enjoy it. First of all buy your tickets from Klook. I actually wasn't able to buy the tickets from the official website. I read that that happens a lot to people from outside of Japan. The days are color coded according to how busy they are expected to be and the prices differ as well. Try to opt for a day that isn't too crowded. We chose the middle out of 5 levels and it was overall ok, even though it was a Saturday. I would also highly recommend a fast pass package. There are many options and it can be confusing so some research to determine which rides you want to go on and which areas you want to access is unfortunately essential. The fast pass gives you timed access to some areas like Super Nintendo World and Harry Potter, which are the two most crowded as well as access to the fast track line for one of the rides in those areas and other rides as well. An important tip is that the park opens about an hour before the stated time for that day. So people actually show up 2 hours before the official opening time to get a good spot in the queue and when they do open they rush usually to Super Nintendo World. You don't need a timed access before the park \"officially\" opens. You could also rush to an area where you don't have a later timed entry already. Alternatively you can check the app and book a timed entry or find staff who hand out timed entry tickets. Both of those have to be done in the park on the day of your visit. I personally opted for a timed entry to Super Nintendo World and a fast pass for Mario Kart and another for Harry Potter and one of the roller coasters as well as the Jaws ride and another roller coaster. There are many options on Klook but take care that they sell out very early. So buy them in advance. The rides are all fun and there are a lot of shows as well. There are plenty of food options too. I had a pizza near the Jaws ride and a nice strawberry dessert from a Super Mario themed cafe. My favorite area was Super Nintendo World. The Donkey Kong ride was a very long wait, but worth it in my opinion. Try to get a fast pass for that if you book early enough. Overall a busy but enjoyable day.",
