            title: "Book your passes waaay before you go.",
            rating: 5,
            helpfulVotes: 1,
            text: "Please, please, please. Book a week to a month before your planned visit because passes WILL run out. I forgot about that and booked a day before so we were left with the regular passes. I had a 3 and a 6yr old with me so the 3yr old came in for free. Also, book on Klook.. they might offer the passes a bit cheaper compared to the website. And they have packages as well.. like the one with the \"Have fun in Kansai\" pass which let's you ride the train from Kansai airport for free.\nStudy the passes and their packages and see what suits you.. might be Nintendo world, Harry potter or Donkey Kong.\nDownload the app! But you won't be able to use it unless you're inside USJ. We, who only had the regular passes had to hustle inside and use the app immediately so that we could pick a time for Nintendo world. Yes, there will be time slots available but it WILL run out fast. So, pick the earliest time available and book it right away. \nPackages with specific fast passes to rides is essential especially if you enjoy rides. Average wait times will be 30-45 mins, or can even go up to an hour. So pick your rides. I went to the flying dinosaur and waited about 30mins. Fast pass cuts that time by 80% so I saw people pass me by and just skipped the line.\nFun rides for adrenaline rushers will be Flying Dinosaur,  Hollywood dream and Hollywood backdrop. Mid-rides will be DKs country, Mario kart, Harry potter etc.\nTip: Elmo's ride sits only toddlers up to kindergarten age. So if your kid is a first grader just say he's still in kindergarten. Enjoy!",
