            rating: 1,
            helpfulVotes: 0,
            text: "We visited as a family, mum, dad and 11 year old son.\n\nStaying in a hotel in Dotonbori, getting to and from Universal Studios was super easy using the metro.. this is one of the few positive things about this day out.\n\nWe did not buy premium passes and instead decided to arrive just before 8am.  After queuing to get in (be sure to take sun umbrellas and plenty of water in summer as you will spend much time queuing in direct sunlight) a fast-paced walk/jog directly to Nintendo World paid off as we were able to get entry to that section of the park without queuing, be sure to get there first thing if you want to achieve the same.. sadly this is where things go down hill.. we only aimed to get on one ride in this area.. ‚ÄòMinecraft madness‚Äô.. sadly the queuing time was just over 3 hours!! (after initial signs stating 2 hours) Had it not been summer we probably would have stuck it out.. but.. despite the considerable effort of Universal Studios to keep the place cool the summer weather was just too much unless you have at least 3 litres of water per person whilst queuing for the ride + previously mentioned sun umbrella(s).. we waited an hour and gave up.. much to my sons dismay.. it just wasn‚Äôt worth the potential heat-related health problems (and we‚Äôre not unfit/overweight etc).\n\nWe went on to discover that all the proper rides had similar wait times.. in the end we watched the ‚ÄòSing‚Äô show which was about 20mins of furry animal costumes mostly lip syncing.. fun but not talented.  \n\nOne very positive thing I have to say is that all the park staff are very friendly and helpful so that was really great :)\n\nUnfortunately the food options are not good.  Unless you really want to spend more than most families would consider reasonable (even expected) for a theme park or get anything like ‚Äòproper‚Äô food.. just take your own.. you‚Äôll be very glad you did.  Drinks are available all over which is great but food is very sparse and poor and very overpriced.\n\nAlthough we were able to get some good photos from around the park and enjoyed checking out the shops (again the usual theme park premium applies) we sadly came away having gone on zero rides due to the excessive wait times (although this would have been less of a problem if the temperature was sub 30 degrees), this is obviously caused by the park allowing way, WAY more people than the park can reasonably accommodate.. we left feeling very much like we‚Äôd been sold an experience that would never have been possible to deliver due to visitor numbers.. if you do go and you have the money.. definitely spend the extra on premium passes to avoid disappointment..",
