            id: "1024630772",
            title: "Absolutely rammed - even express tickets queued my 40 mins",
            rating: 3,
            helpfulVotes: 0,
            text: "Went with family of six on a Friday in August.  Took the MRT to hat outside and then taking 4 escalators up joined the sensors express (Monorail) to the resort work stop.  Tickets for the Sentosa express are 4 dollars per person.  Children U7 free - you can buy at the monorail entrance or simply use your MRT card at the gate to save buying a ticket.  (Return is free - you only need a racket to get out to the island). \n\nArrived at 9:40 at the universal entrance and the queue was quite small - 50 people in each of 6 lines. We entered the park and headed to minions land (we had standard park tickets), and we managed to go on 3 minions land rides in just 75 minutes, amazing as later in the day all these had +50 min ride waits. We then headed to far far away land and did shred 4d and the magic potion spin both within the next hour. \n\nA brief stop for lunch and then back to enchanted airways - but the queue was 60 mins due to so many express pass riders being let in early.  This is a very short ride and not worth the queue.\n\nWe then headed to the rapids (80 min queue), again massively impacted by the fast pass riders being let in first. \n\nIt was 3:30 by this time so a stop for more drinks and refills, before we went on Accelerator, then Lights, Camera Action and a walk in the shops.  We headed back to Cyclon (queue said 60 mins but only took 20 mins - the best ride on the park), and Treasure Hunters. \n\nOn the way out at 6:30 we spotted Transformers 3D was open and made this our last ride of the day.\n\nOverall thoughts: the park is good, more aimed at smaller kids, some rides very similar to small UK theme parks. \n\nPasses/ if you buy a standard pass, it‚Äôs almost impossible to do all the rides you want to go on due to horrendous queues. Some queues were 120 mins and many others were 70 mins.  \n\nIf you buy and express pass there are also rides with queues - rapids was 59 min queue even for the express pass for example (a staff member has a sign warning people).\n\nThe overall experience is that the park is ok, but massively oversold with people. Some of the staff are strict and rude, the prices for food and drinks and super high, and the ride turnaround is slow (single staff members loading cars, operating the queues and also controlling the start/stop slowed things down where it could have been quicker. \n\nTips: take some food and drinks - despite all signs about bag searches we didn‚Äôt see a single bag searched when we entered. \n\nTips: rapids has a singe rider line - use this to save 2 hours of queuing if you can.\n\nTips: you can complete minion land in the first hour if you arrive early.\n\nTips:  barge your MET cars up the day before to avoid having to buy a monorail ticket.\n\nTips:  stay late - the queues get smaller in the last 90 mins.",
