            rating: 4,
            helpfulVotes: 1,
            text: "Just got back from a visit to Universal Studios Singapore and thought I‚Äôd clear up some misinformation I saw in other reviews ‚Äî not because people are wrong, but because things have changed, and most reviews are outdated. Here‚Äôs what you need to know if you‚Äôre visiting as of July 2025. \n\nEXPRESS VS EXPRESS PLUS\nThe main difference now is Minion Land. If you want to skip the queue at the main Minion ride, you‚Äôll need the Express Plus pass. Regular Express doesn‚Äôt cover it.\n\nThat said, even on a busy day, the wait time for the Minion kiddie rides was under 10 minutes, and about 50 minutes for the main ride. Personally, I‚Äôd save the S$30 and just:\n\t‚Ä¢\tBe there when the park opens,\n\t‚Ä¢\tHead straight to Minion Land,\n\t‚Ä¢\tRide the Minion attraction first,\n\t‚Ä¢\tThen use a regular Express pass for everything else.\n\nEXPRESS LINE = NOT INSTANT\nAnother thing: the Express line isn‚Äôt always ‚Äúskip the queue.‚Äù We still waited 20+ minutes at rides like Revenge of the Mummy and Transformers. But hey ‚Äî that‚Äôs still better than the regular 60‚Äì90 min lines.\n\nFREE WATER (SORT OF)\nYou can get free water all over the park from drinking fountains, but it‚Äôs warm. The trick? Ask food vendors for free ice, or use self-service ice machines at larger food courts. Bring your own bottle or cup and boom ‚Äî free iced water all day.\n\nFOOD & PAYMENT\nThey say no outside food or drinks, but no one checked. Having a few snacks and your own water bottle will save you time and money.\nAlso important: The park is fully cashless, so bring a credit or debit card ‚Äî no cash accepted anywhere\n\nWe had a great day, but I do think they oversell the Express pass a little. It‚Äôs still worth it for cutting down wait times, but manage your expectations ‚Äî and skip the Plus unless Minions are a must-do.\n\nPS : Waterworld show was still closed when we visited.",
